<h3> NOTES </h3>

OBLIGE was written from scratch. It does not contain any code
from SLIGE (by David Chess) or from any other random level
generator.

<p>
OBLIGE uses a modified version of the Lua 5.1.5 scripting
language, which is Copyright 1994-2012 Lua.org, PUC-Rio, and is
is under a permissive "MIT" license.  The original version can
be found here: <a href="http://www.lua.org/">www.lua.org</a>

<p>
Part of the cave algorithm used in OBLIGE was described by Jim Babcock
in his article: "Cellular Automata Method for Generating
Random Cave-Like Levels".

<p>
OBLIGE uses the FLTK widget library:
<a href="http://www.fltk.org">www.fltk.org</a>


